description: |
  Accessibility patterns and best practices for Vue.js applications with CoreUI, including ARIA attributes, keyboard navigation, and screen reader support.
globs:
  - src/**/*.vue
  - src/assets/scss/**/*.scss
alwaysApply: true
rules:
  # ARIA Attributes
  - Use proper ARIA attributes for form elements
  - Implement proper ARIA labels and descriptions
  - Use proper ARIA roles and states
  - Follow the established ARIA patterns

  # Keyboard Navigation
  - Implement proper keyboard navigation
  - Use proper tab order and focus management
  - Use proper keyboard event handling
  - Follow the established keyboard navigation patterns

  # Screen Reader Support
  - Use proper semantic HTML elements
  - Implement proper screen reader announcements
  - Use proper alt text for images
  - Follow the established screen reader patterns

  # Form Accessibility
  - Use proper form labels and associations
  - Implement proper form validation announcements
  - Use proper form error handling
  - Follow the established form accessibility patterns

  # Color and Contrast
  - Use proper color contrast ratios
  - Implement proper color accessibility
  - Use proper color coding alternatives
  - Follow the established color accessibility patterns

  # Focus Management
  - Use proper focus management
  - Implement proper focus trapping
  - Use proper focus indicators
  - Follow the established focus management patterns

